to walk. Many expats often see this as inconvenient especially those who have family attending schools in Brunei. But if there is any advice that anyone visiting Brunei should be able to remember is to walk.

Walking for 15 minutes in Brunei’s heat is the equivalent of 4 hours on a treadmill in a colder climate. But for those who are still looking for other alternatives besides walking there are two bus lines that will take you closest to the shopping centers. The bus lines are 201 and 202 which can be taken from Papa’s lapang.

Remember, the fun factor of each place depends entirely on your own personal helps and guides. So if you want to visit the Radisson to see their Gold closure. Or walk towards Taman Tasek because if its OASIS (OverLapping Aquatic Sensorial Experience) you’ll find the taxi’s located close to the entrance that can be taken to the destination point of choice.
